 3.1 Local Geology 
 Bedrock  geology  of  the  eastern  tenement  group  comprising  Exploration  Licence  15/625  and 
 related  prospecting  licences  is  largely  masked  by  a  sequence  of  transported  sediments, 
 particularly in northern  areas.   In this  northern sector, cover  sediments  variously composed  of 
 clay, sand, pebble and gravel horizons overlie a basal gravel unit. This cover sequence can vary 
 in thickness from a few metres up to 90 metres, particularly where palaeochannels occur.  To the 
 south  over  central  and  southern  sectors  of  the  area,  komatiitic  basalt,  metadolerite  and  felsic 
 volcaniclastic sediments crop out but because of the masking effects of cover rocks, the nature 
 and structure of the bedrock geology relies on the interpretation of remote sensing surveys and 
 the direct evidence from drilling.
